flowRoot.flowPara: This talk presents the fundamental concepts and methodologies for digital image processing. We will introduce the OpenCV image processing library to build a document scanning application. We will also cover technical details behind basic image processing concepts and filters such as image denoising, image enhancement, and spatial filters.

Building upon the basics of image processing, this talk tackles the problem of image understanding. We will explore ways of information extraction from images and analyze several applications related to content-based retrieval systems and image mining.
